                            <comment id="17125710" author="kgyrtkirk" created="Thu, 4 Jun 2020 09:01:38 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;LGTM: +1&lt;br/&gt;
some notes: ReadEntity#equals violates basic principles (it&apos;s not an equals)&lt;br/&gt;
I&apos;m no expert in the area but at first glance I don&apos;t think that the cases when the mergeIsDirectFlag is false are doing any good: I&apos;m adding 2 inputs: one with direct and one with direct off - the result depends on which one I&apos;ve added first?&lt;br/&gt;
cc &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=pvary&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;pvary&quot;&gt;pvary&lt;/a&gt; &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17126047" author="nareshpr" created="Thu, 4 Jun 2020 16:15:31 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Incase on select on view, there will be 2 ReadEntity..&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;1 for view with noParent &amp;amp; isDirect is true, 2nd for underlying table with view as parent &amp;amp; isDirect is false.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Same will be validated while preparing privObject&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/hive/blob/master/ql/src/java/org/apache/hadoop/hive/ql/security/authorization/command/CommandAuthorizerV2.java#L106-L109&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/hive/blob/master/ql/src/java/org/apache/hadoop/hive/ql/security/authorization/command/CommandAuthorizerV2.java#L106-L109&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;ie., Incase of view, underlying table/view privs need not to be verified. Only parent view privs to be checked for user.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
